#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Filters/OpenTURNS/README.md:1
msgid "VTK::FiltersOpenTURNS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Filters/OpenTURNS/README.md:3
msgid ""
"This module is based on the OpenTURNS library, which is LGPL licensed. There "
"are some dependencies of OpenTURNS under the GPL license, namely:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Filters/OpenTURNS/README.md:5
msgid ""
"the optional hmat library, under GPL but with an explicit exception for its "
"use within OpenTURNS. This dependency can be deactivated as no part of "
"OpenTURNS used by the VTK module depends on hmat. By the way, the authors of "
"hmat are in the exact same department as the authors of OpenTURNS coming "
"from Airbus"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Filters/OpenTURNS/README.md:6
msgid ""
"the poissoninv set of functions for the efficient computation of the Poisson "
"quantile function. This dependency is mandatory and is used within OpenTURNS "
"with a written exception to the GPL license from the author"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Filters/OpenTURNS/README.md:7
msgid ""
"the KolmogorovSmirnovDist set of functions for the efficient computation of "
"the exact Kolmogorov-Smirnov distribution. This dependency is mandatory and "
"is used within OpenTURNS with a written exception to the GPL license from "
"the author."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Filters/OpenTURNS/README.md:9
msgid ""
"This module (and VTK) cannot be considered to be under the GPL license when "
"using OpenTURNS through the API, since it is an LGPL library which has "
"solved the issue of merging GPL and LGPL code. Thanks to the authors of "
"these dependencies, they are NOT under GPL when used by OpenTURNS!"
msgstr ""
